    "description": "The BreadCrumb by Rajant Corporation is an 802.11 (Wi-Fi) and Ethernet compatible wireless mesh networking device that allows for rapid deployment of mobile wireless networks in a wide variety of environments. It is lightweight, capable of communicating via up to four different radio frequencies, and is designed to be completely mobile as carried by a vehicle or an individual. BreadCrumb devices automatically detect other BreadCrumb devices and dynamically route packets through the resulting wireless mesh on behalf of commercially available off-the-shelf client devices.",
